Do firms lobby politicians by patronizing their businesses?

The case of Berlusconi's media empire

Silvio Berlusconi owned a controlling stake in Mediaset, a media company with several broadcast TV channels in Italy, while he served as Prime Minister. Mediaset TV ad rates were consistently higher during his terms in office. Desha Cam/Bigstock

Most research on the role of money in politics has focused on direct contributions
